            <para>The procedure for installing the charge air coolers is included with this letter.</para>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>PROCEDURE FOR INSTALLING MODINE SERVICE CAC ON 9400, 5000, 8100, 8200, 8300, 2500 AND 2600 SERIES
                VEHICLES
            </title>
            <svcprocinfo>
                <para>The procedures described below are for replacing charge air cooler part numbers: 1674000C1 and
                    1674001C1.
                </para>
            </svcprocinfo>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>8100</title>
                <para>The charge air cooler for the 8100, Part Number 1674332C1 and its mounting do not change.</para>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>8200, 8300, 2500, 2600 and 5000SFA</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove old charge air cooler.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position new charge air cooler on the studs on top of the radiator.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Secure the lower end of the charge air cooler to the mounting bracket on the
                        radiator.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install and tighten the nuts on the six studs on top of the charge air cooler to
                        140-190 in-lbs. (16-21 Nm).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Before re-installing the radiator re-circulation seal, test install it to check for
                        clearance at the radius on both ends. It may be necessary to trim a slight bit of material from
                        both ends to make the seal fit properly.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Re-install all the components removed to gain access to the top of the radiator.
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>9400 and 5000SBA</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove old charge air cooler.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position new charge air cooler on the studs (Item 3,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9312071">Figure 1</hotlnk>) on top of the radiator.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Secure the lower end of the charge air cooler to the mounting bracket on the
                        radiator.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Drill two 11/32 inch diameter holes through the top channel of the radiator at each
                        end of the charge air cooler (Item 4,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9312071">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                        <emph type="bold">Care should be taken not to drill into the radiator core.</emph>
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>A drill bit stop should be used to prevent accidently drilling into the radiator core.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install 3/8-16 x 5/8 inch Tap-Tite (self tapping) Hex Washer Hd. Screws (supplied
                        with the CAC) in the four holes drilled in step 4.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the four screws to 144 in-lbs. (16.266 Nm).</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install and tighten the nuts on the two studs (Item 3,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9312071">Figure 1</hotlnk>) to 140-190 in-lbs. (16-21 Nm).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Before re-installing the radiator re-circulation seal, test install it to check for
                        clearance at the radius on both ends. It may be necessary to trim a slight bit of material from
                        both ends to make the seal fit properly.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Re-install all the components removed to gain access to the top of the radiator.
                    </para>
                </step1>
